body:
@thedarkknight197 that is correct. We need more than one signer to seal blocks on POA network; 
1 signer is **not enough** for decentralization, try adding more sealers to your Proof-of-Authority network. 

To add more signers, enter geth console then run command `clique.propose("0x.....", true)` where as 0x..... is the etherbase of Node2, i.e your miners public wallet address. 

Good luck
